  "body": "#### System information\n\nGeth version: `1.5.0-unstable-4dc45770` (swarm branch)\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 16.04\n#### Expected behaviour\n\nI upload a file to my swarm node using http proxy. I expect to get back the swarm-root-hash of the file.\n`cat /path/to/large/file | curl -X POST -d @- http://localhost:32200/bzzr:/ && echo`\nshould always return the same hash. \n#### Actual behaviour\n\nWhen the network is slow, I get a different incorrect hash every time.\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\n\nI had to simulate a network delay on localhost to get this to work.\n`sudo tc qdisc add dev lo root handle 1:0 netem delay 100msec`\n\nand then do\n\n`for i in 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 9 0; do cat /path/to/large/file | curl -X POST -d @- http://192.168.1.125:32200/bzzr:/ && echo; done` \n\nyou will get 10 different hashes.\n\nyou can reset your network using\n`sudo tc qdisc del dev lo root`\n",
